FBIS4-40817 "drsov119_a_94019" FBIS-SOV-94-119 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Invites Italy's Berlusconi to Visit Moscow Invites Italy's Berlusconi to Visit Moscow LD2006164994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1539 GMT 20 Jun 94 LD2006164994 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Alexey Bukalov and Alexey Golayev] [Text] Milan June 20 TASS--Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi met with visiting Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin in Milan on Monday to discuss bilateral relations. The meeting became one of the key events in Chernomyrdin's schedule. The Russian premier is in Milan to attend the World Gas Congress. Chernomyrdin said that the "treaty of friendship and cooperation between Russia and Italy is ready for signing." It is time for the head of the Italian Government to visit Moscow, he said. Chernomyrdin's talks with Berlusconi is the first contact of the Russian leadership with the new Italian premier. The meeting gave good opportunities for a free exchange of views on bilateral relations and international issues. The talks between Chernomyrdin and Berlusconi have started a new stage in Russia's contacts with the leaders of the leading industrialised countries following recent meetings with U.S. President Bill Clinton and German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in light of the upcoming G-7 summit meeting to be held in Naples in July which will be attended by Russia.
